# This repo has no non-secret config, so `.env` is optional — but the loaders
# still call load_dotenv(), so create an (empty) one if you like:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# --- Your API keys are NOT stored here or in .env ---
# Store them in your OS keychain and inject them per-command with `secrun`
# (2-minute setup: ../SECRETS.md), then run scripts as:
#   secrun python examples/...
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#   VOYAGE_API_KEY     https://www.voyageai.com/   (optional — only examples/12_embeddings.py)
# (.env is in .gitignore regardless; never commit it.)

